Task #2: Vercel Deployment Configuration (final)

Complete Vercel deployment support while keeping Replit/VPS behavior unchanged.

Architecture:
- server/app.ts: shared Express app factory (createApp + log)
- server/index.ts: traditional entry - adds Vite/static serving, binds to port 5000
- api/index.ts: Vercel serverless entry - singleton app, calls serveStatic in production

Key files:
- vercel.json: routes with handle:filesystem (CDN for static assets, Express for API + SPA fallback)
- server/db.ts: DB pool capped at 2 on Vercel (VERCEL=1), configurable via DB_POOL_MAX
- server/routes.ts: session pool also capped consistently with app DB pool on Vercel
- server/static.ts: VERCEL-aware distPath (__dirname/../dist/public on Vercel)
- package.json: vercel-build = npm run build (full build: Vite + esbuild server bundle)
- DEPLOYMENT.md: full step-by-step Vercel guide with env vars, troubleshooting, build notes

Post-review fixes:
1. vercel-build now runs npm run build (not just vite build)
2. Unmatched routes forwarded to Express via routes + handle:filesystem (not /index.html directly)
3. Removed as any casts - uses typed NodeHandler alias with as unknown as
4. Session pool in routes.ts now respects DB_POOL_MAX / Vercel cap (was uncapped at 10)
5. DEPLOYMENT.md corrected to describe actual build process (script/build.ts)
